Paediatric Surgery deals with the disease, trauma and malformations of childhood years (foetal period to teenage years and young adults).

This programme is run by the South East School of Surgery

programmeSections.cardSummary: This means you will have to first complete a core programme, and then  apply and complete this subspecialism/higher training to gain your CCT.

Programme structure

This is a chance to show some content about Paediatric surgery programmes that apply nationally.

This is a paragraph explaining any Local area-specific information regarding the structure of this programme.

Rotations

The trainees have either their first two years at Alder Hey Hospital or at Manchester Children’s Hospital, then their next two years at the other hospital. The final two years (ST7, ST8) are split between Manchester Children's Hospital and Alder Hey Hospital depending on training/subspeciality needs

Paediatric urology training will be two 6 month blocks; one in ST4-5 and one in ST6-7.

Both sites provide basic and advanced training in general paediatric surgery and urology. Between them they can provide both basic and specialised training e.g. bladder exstrophy, short bowel management oncology and stone management services.

programmeSections.cardSummary: Applications for the next academic year will open on 20 April 2021
programmeSections.mainBody:
How do I apply?

To train in this specialism, you will need to have completed core surgery training. You will need to apply before the application deadline of the year you will start.

If applications are open, you can use the button below to start filling out your application. You will need to have an idea of which programmes at which deanery you would prefer to study.

How to plan your application

Neurosurgery deals with the prevention, diagnosis, surgical treatment, and rehabilitation of disorders which affect any portion of the nervous system including the brain, spinal cord, central and peripheral nervous system, and cerebrovascular system.
